data.title: First French Empire
data.text:
The First French Empire was a former country in Europe, that existed from 1804 to 1815, it was against the Coalition during Napoleonic Wars. It is often grouped into the same person as First French Republic.

Appearance[ç¼–è¾‘ | ç¼–è¾‘æºä»£ç ]

The First French Empire often shown wearing a simplified version of Napoleon's soldiers: a black bicorn hat with a blue jacket with golden epaulettes, golden sleeves, a small golden chain with a white short trouser, and black boots.

The First French Empire is depicted as both a man and a woman.

Their body can be all white, but also sometimes the left arm can be blue and the right one red: due to the flag's stripes.

Personality[ç¼–è¾‘ | ç¼–è¾‘æºä»£ç ]

Like the Roman Empire, the First French Empire stands out for a change in personality over time. From being most of the time haughty, who doesn't stand most of the time any joke about them while they love making fun of others, to be a much more understanding person with others, moved by the expansion of the economic liberalism, industrial revolution, education, arts, and laws throughout Europe. This same personality is usually applied to other European powers of the time such as: the Portuguese Empire, Prussia, Russian Empire, Spanish Empire or Sweden.

History[ç¼–è¾‘ | ç¼–è¾‘æºä»£ç ]

End of the First Republic and beginning of the Empire[ç¼–è¾‘ | ç¼–è¾‘æºä»£ç ]

In 1804, the First French Empire was proclaimed on the territory of the First French Republic.

In April-August 1805, the III anti-French coalition was formed, consisting of Russia, Great Britain, Austria, Sweden and Kingdom of Sicily. On December 2, 1805, the highly famous Battle of Austerlitz took place on Austrian territory, also going down in history as the Battle of Three Emperors. The French Empire won, which is why Austria withdrew from the Third Anti-French Coalition and signed the Peace of Presburg with First French Empire, Russian troops retreated. The III anti-French coalition collapsed, and the Holy Roman Empire ceased to exist.

In 1806, the IV anti-French coalition was formed, the members of which were Great Britain, the Kingdom of Prussia, the Russian Empire, the File:Kingdom of Saxony-Pictogram.png Kingdom of Saxony and Sweden. On October 1, 1806, Kingdom of Prussia presented an ultimatum to First French Empire, but it was rejected, as a result of which the War of the Fourth Coalition began. The Kingdom of Prussia suffered defeat after defeat, the battles of Schleitz, Saalfeld, Jena and Auerstedt were lost, and on October 27 the French Empire took Berlin. The Treaties of Tilsit are signed, the IV coalition is defeated.

Treaties of Tilsit[ç¼–è¾‘ | ç¼–è¾‘æºä»£ç ]

Franco-Russian Treaty[ç¼–è¾‘ | ç¼–è¾‘æºä»£ç ]

On June 25th, 1807, First French Empire and Russian Empire meet on the Neman (a river in-between French Warsaw and the Russian Empire). On July 7th however, the actual treaty is signed. The terms that Russian Empire had to oblige to included, joining the Continental System (not being allowed to trade with the British), giving up the Ionian Islands and Cattaro (now known as Kotor), enter an Anglo-Russian war, and try and bring Swedish Empire into the continental system as well.

For First French Empire, they agreed to aid Russian Empire against Ottoman Empire, as well as guarantee the sovereignty of various small states ruled by Kingdom of Prussia.

Not all terms are followed. Without the ability to trade with British Empire, Russian Empire's economy faced some issues. So, Russian Empire traded with the British behind First French Empire's back. Plus, First French Empire did not provide support against Ottoman Empire.

The treaty ended on December 31st, 1810.
